description:
All adventure, all action, for all ages!

Join Spider-Man, Iron Man and Hulk as they team up against the fiercest obstacles and most dangerous villains they've ever encountered. Featuring the Incredible Hercules; Kang the Conqueror; Klaw, The Master of Sound; Meteor Men from out space; and more!

Collecting Marvel Adventures Super Heroes #1-4, written by Paul Tobin and illustrated by Alvin Lee.
name: Marvel Adventures Spider-Man, Hulk, and Iron Man: Triple Threat

volume.name: Marvel Adventures Spider-Man, Hulk & Iron Man: Triple Threat

description: A standalone prequel to this summer's most anticipated movie! Colonel John 'Hannibal' Smith is never stuck for a plan. But how is he going to cope with a mission in which everything goes wrong and he might just wind up on the wrong side of Saddam Hussein in this Desert Storm flashback adventure we're calling... 'The Luckiest Man In Iraq.'
name: The Luckiest Man In Iraq

description: Includes a story about Nick Fury and character sketches.

The history books tell us that young Prince Namor, the proud son of an Atlantean princess, joined the Allied fight against the Nazis in order to protect his undersea people. But what if Namor grew up on land with his human father, filled with hatred for the Atlanteans who killed his mother? For whom will he fight when World War II sweeps the planet and Atlantis calls for help? And in what terrifying ways might the course of history be changed forever?
name: What if Prince Namor of Atlantis... grew up on land?
